title: For Sale/Trade:  GREAT BREAKING NEWS!
postcontent:
Indiana: House Passes NRA-Backed Hunting Reform 

Today, House Bill 1563 passed the Indiana House of Representatives by an overwhelming 95-2 vote. HB1563 will now be transferred to the Senate where it will be referred to the appropriate Senate committee for consideration.

HB 1563, sponsored by state Representative Sean Eberhart (R-57) and fully supported by the Indiana Department of Natural Resources, would allow hunters in Indiana to use lawfully-possessed suppressors (also referred to as silencers) on firearms while hunting.

Noise complaints are being used more frequently as an excuse to close shooting ranges, informal shooting areas and hunting lands throughout the country. Increased use of suppressors will help to eliminate many of these complaints and protect hunting and shooting areas well into the future.

While suppressors do not eliminate the sound of a firearm, they do reduce the muzzle report in a manner similar to the way that a muffler reduces exhaust noise from a vehicle. The benefits associated with suppressor use include increased accuracy due to reduced recoil and muzzle blast, protection from hearing damage and reduced noise pollution.

The NRA would like to thank Representative Eberhart and Speaker Brian Bosma (R-88) for ensuring the passage of this pro-hunting reform. Please stay tuned to NRA-ILA | ILA Home for updates on the status of this legislation as it progresses through the Senate.

title: For Sale:  1945 Springfield Armory M1 Garand Package
postcontent: This is a completely re-done Springfield Armory M1 Garand (3.6 million serial, April 1945) in 30.06. All parts are SA except the barrel, which has been replaced with an absolutely mint Danish VAR 1966 barrel. The VAR barrel is proofed and marked properly. These barrels are reknown in the M1 world as phenomenal shooters and this one gauges with a TE of 0.9 and an ME of 0.9 on Fulton gauges, which is new. Try finding a Danish VAR barrel that gauges under 1 on both ends; it's not easy. The bore is mirror-like and crisp, with a perfect crown. Here are the drawing numbers for key parts: receiver serial# 366XXXX, drawing number D28291 35 heat lot O81B; barrel D6535448 4-66 VAR; bolt D28287-19SA; op rod D35382 9 SA; trigger housing D28290 18 SA; hammer C46008-7 SA; safety SA 11; elev knob WCE; windage knob BME. This rifle is nearly correct per Scott Duff's book: M1 Garand Serial Numbers and Data Sheets. The M1 has brand new gorgeous natural walnut stock and handguards. The finish matches on all the wood, and it's not shiny. Just natural USGI look. All small pins and springs have been replaced, op-rod spring replaced, and the entire M1 was re-parked in manganese phosphate, down to the handguard metal. Headspaced and timing block checked, then test fired with Greek HXP. This M1 is as close to “new off the rack” as you can get. Nicer than the ones Miltech offers for $1600+ and they don't include the items in this package. It’s simply gorgeous and you’ll agree when you see it. Here's the package: 1945 SA M1 Garand w/like new Danish barrel; Turner Saddlery Black All-Weather 1903 style sling; CMP hard case; repro Garand soft case; nearly $200 in At The Front web gear - cartridge belt, reinforced suspenders, first aid pouch - outstanding web gear made to original specs; nearly $800 in USGI and Fulton Armory spare parts to keep this rifle running a long time - USGI spares include two complete bolt assemblies - one is WWII NOS and a NOS gas cylinder. Spares also include a NIB Schuster adjustable gas plug so you can shoot commercial ammo; over $100 in Garand specific tools and cleaning gear including headspace gauges; various Garand books. All items in the package are in like new condition except where noted. You won't find a package like this ANYWHERE - especially these days! Buyer may also contact me about purchasing a SUBSTANTIAL amount of ammo. Payment via personal check. Package ships when payment clears. There will be at least two packages - rifle in the CMP hard case and all other items in at least one other box. Please ensure your FFL will accept this shipment from a private seller.
